{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect Z parameter usage in LDPC decoder offset calculations\n\n### Summary\nThe LDPC decoder generator functions were using a fixed maximum Z value (NR_LDPC_ZMAX = 384) instead of the runtime Z parameter when calculating memory offsets. This caused incorrect memory access patterns when the actual Z value differed from the maximum, leading to unexpected behavior in the generated decoder functions.\n\nThis fix updates the offset calculations to use the runtime Z parameter, ensuring correct memory addressing for all valid Z values.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProcPc_gen_BG1_128.c`: Fixed offset calculation to use runtime Z parameter instead of NR_LDPC_ZMAX.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProcPc_gen_BG2_128.c`: Applied same fix for consistency.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProcPc_gen_BG1_avx2.c`: Fixed offset calculation in AVX2 version.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProcPc_gen_BG2_avx2.c`: Applied same fix for consistency.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProc_gen_BG1_128.c`: Fixed regular bnProc generator.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProc_gen_BG2_128.c`: Fixed BG2 128-bit version.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProc_gen_BG1_avx2.c`: Fixed BG1 AVX2 version.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/bnProc_gen_BG2_avx2.c`: Fixed BG2 AVX2 version.\n\n"
}